00:36:40.399 --> 00:36:43.135 align:middle line:84%
on morphine which you
don't want when you're 11,

00:36:43.135 --> 00:36:46.405 align:middle line:84%
and the pain hadn't been
touched by the morphine,

00:36:46.405 --> 00:36:48.573 align:middle line:84%
did the lightning proceeding
and now he's learning to,

00:36:48.573 --> 00:36:50.676 align:middle line:84%
he thinks he's going to
be championship boxer.

00:36:50.676 --> 00:36:53.478 align:middle line:84%
So he's like, he's back
to health and fitness

00:36:53.478 --> 00:36:56.214 align:middle line:84%
and being punched and in no
pain or the same amount of pain

00:36:56.214 --> 00:36:58.116 align:middle line:90%
as he would after being hit

00:36:58.116 --> 00:37:00.886 align:middle line:84%
but he's completely
functioning normally.

00:37:00.886 --> 00:37:02.888 align:middle line:90%
And when people get well one

00:37:02.888 --> 00:37:05.891 align:middle line:84%
of the things they often say
is it's great to be well.

00:37:05.891 --> 00:37:07.292 align:middle line:90%
It's great to be happy.

00:37:07.292 --> 00:37:10.562 align:middle line:84%
One thing I notice is I notice
the trees and I notice the birds

00:37:10.562 --> 00:37:15.233 align:middle line:84%
and I notice my kids and I'm
breathing and I become aware

00:37:15.233 --> 00:37:17.035 align:middle line:84%
of that moment and I
talk about it in the book

00:37:17.035 --> 00:37:19.104 align:middle line:84%
that very often we're
not present and the kind

00:37:19.104 --> 00:37:22.307 align:middle line:84%
of times we are present is
in those momentous events

00:37:22.307 --> 00:37:24.142 align:middle line:84%
like when somebody
has a kid, a new baby.

00:37:24.142 --> 00:37:28.580 align:middle line:84%
Wow, got a baby and then they
go home from the hospital

00:37:28.580 --> 00:37:30.749 align:middle line:84%
or they go out for the first
time and everyone else seems

00:37:30.749 --> 00:37:32.250 align:middle line:84%
to be carrying on like
nothing's happened,

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.554 align:middle line:84%
like they're just
going to work and going

00:37:35.554 --> 00:37:39.524 align:middle line:84%
to Starbucks eating their
food and I've got a baby.

00:37:39.524 --> 00:37:40.859 align:middle line:90%
The world should be stopped.

00:37:40.859 --> 00:37:43.528 align:middle line:84%
This is such a momentous event
and it's in those moments

00:37:43.528 --> 00:37:46.698 align:middle line:84%
when we're actually present
or another example is

00:37:46.698 --> 00:37:51.003 align:middle line:84%
when you have a near
accident or near bad diagnosis

00:37:51.003 --> 00:37:54.639 align:middle line:84%
and you survive and you
suddenly realize how great it is

00:37:54.639 --> 00:37:55.640 align:middle line:90%
to be alive again.

00:37:55.640 --> 00:37:57.509 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: What a
gift, what a miracle.

